{"questionId":"23a951fb-833f-4b27-9978-4eb054f855e2_10","correctAnswer":"7","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Set up","content":"Equal ratios form a proportion: $$\\frac{154}{110} = \\frac{x}{5}$$"},{"title":"Solve","content":"Cross-multiply: $154 \\times 5 = 110x$, so $770 = 110x$, giving $x = \\frac{770}{110} = 7$."},{"title":"Answer","content":"<strong>7</strong> is correct."}]}